[Affected versions]:
- Firefox 60.0.2, 61.0b13, nightly 62.0a1 (2018-06-13), 
Firefox-45.3.0esr, 61.0b7DevEd

[Affected platforms]:
- Win 10x64, macOS 10.13.4; Ubuntu 16.04LTS.

[Steps to reproduce]:
1. Launch Firefox;
2. Open the Developer Tools(F12 key), enable the Canvas tool;
3. Access the following link: http://fabricjs.com/
4. Click the Reload button;
5. Click the Record button;
6. Grab on any object from the page and move it around;
7. Click inside the Filter Calls section;
8. Type anything;
9. Click on the Reset (x) button.

[Expected result]:
- Filter box and displayed results are reset.

[Actual result]:
- The results are not reset, filtered ones are displayed.

[Regression range]:
- does not seem to be a regression, managed to reproduce on v.45;
- will investigate further if/when needed.

[Additional notes]:
- deleting them clears the list;
- attached screenshot with the button in cause.
